JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC, Panyaza Lesufi says he was saddened to learn about the arrest of a schooler bus driver for  allegations of sexual assault. It is alleged that a 44 year-old bus driver sexually assaulted a 13 year-old pupil on two occasions.  READ: Gauteng Education Department, police to meet with school guards Condemns the alleged sexual assault by a Gauteng bus driver against a 13-year-old pupil. #MeToo #365DaysofActivism @GovernmentZA The case aws reported by the pupil and a teacher and the alleged perpetrator was arrested on Friday. He is due to appear in court on Monday. Lesufi said, "Unfortunately, he will never be allowed in our schooling environment, these activities will not be allowed to prevail in our space." eNCA